text.text: Mahamaya temple is situated in Ambika pur near about 2 kms from bus stand. This temple is made by maharaja sarguja Raghunathsharan . This is called mahamaya temple in the name of goddess ambika and this place Ambikapur is also called in the name of goddess ambika. This temple is very old and it is the time of kalchuri kal .This was built in between 1879 to 1917 in Nagar shaili .It’s shape is just like a mandap pattern. When we visit this  holy temple we feel very internal peace in mind.

text.text: Locally known as Raghunath Palace, it is the palace of royal dynasty of Ambikapur. The palace still stands on its firm ground due to its marvellous architectural design. The palace has rich historical importance in Chhattisgarh context. One must visit this place when in Ambikapur. The palace also has hotel attached which is owned by the his majesty the king himself- Shri T.S. Singh Deo.

text.text:
Surguja Palace named Raghunath Palace is one of the palaces of India which have rich history and a great legacy behind them to explore and be informed about.
With a unique architecture it attracts and radiates it's glory of past ages. It has a very rich museum which is full of historical artifacts.
Dussehra (दसहरा) is still observed with much fanfare in the precincts of this magnificent Palace building. Pooja (पूजा) for the specific day is observed by the present Maharaja Shri Tribhuvaneshwar Saran Singh Deo, popularly called as T.S.Baba by the masses.

text.text: The Maharaja Palace is the historical palace of Ambikapur, the history of the princely state of surguja has been very glorious.  What makes this history even richer is the Raghunath Palace, the palace here.  This palace has seen the golden period of the princely state of Surguja.  Whose testimony gives its rate and wall.  But with time, this palace has now become a palace to cherish the old memories. This palace was built long before 1895.  But in 1895, facing north, it was given a complete shape and this palace was named Raghunath Palace after the then Maharaja of Surguja, Raghunath Sharan Singhdeo.  This palace holds thousands of memories.  With the passing time, the palace has also become old.  The walls are cracked but it's amazing nonetheless.  A wonderful heritage can be felt on seeing it. The credit of making this palace and the best decoration in it goes to Maharani Vijayeshwari.  Maharani Vijeshwari was from the Nepal royal family.

text.text:
Dadi Rani Sati Temple Ambikapur,
The temple is a symbol of history of Rajasthan where there was a lady known as Narayani Devi (Dadi Rani Sati) who committed Sati on her husband's death with some more lady who lost her husband in a war,
The story was between the 13th to the 17th century.
There are many temples in Northwest India but one is very famous for Dadi Rani Sati temple was in Jhunjhunu Rajasthan.
